  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The SAIL GPIO driver provides interfaces to configure, read input/output values, and write output values to a GPIO."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A GPIO is configured as input/output or as a special function GPIO."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The GPIO driver also supports receiving interrupts from GPIO. Interrupts are generated as level triggered, rising edge, falling edge, or dual edge triggered."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "SAIL provide 79 GPIOs: SAIL[0]-SAIL[78] on QAM8255 and QAM8775."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Configure%20SAIL%20Port/image-2024-11-4_20-31-37.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Configure SAIL Port/image-2024-11-4_20-31-37.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "SAIL GPIO/TLMM does not have a concept of ports. Therefore, one port corresponds to one channel. As a result, DioPortId and DioChannelID should be the same in symbolic value generation."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "GPIO Tools:"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Configure%20SAIL%20Port/image-2024-10-22_16-28-12.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Configure SAIL Port/image-2024-10-22_16-28-12.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Pin Configuration Tool"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Qualcomm pin configuration tool is available in CreatePoint to help customers with QUP assignments and avoid conflicts."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Link: Qualcomm Pin Configuration Tool"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Need your account check in."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "1. How to configure port for Uart ?"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1.1. check schematic diagram， SAIL_IO_6/7 used."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Configure%20SAIL%20Port/image-2024-10-22_15-6-9.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Configure SAIL Port/image-2024-10-22_15-6-9.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1.2. PortNumber: It defines the port number of SAIL domain."
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Configure%20SAIL%20Port/image-2024-10-22_15-15-29.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Configure SAIL Port/image-2024-10-22_15-15-29.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Configure%20SAIL%20Port/image-2024-10-22_15-16-37.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Configure SAIL Port/image-2024-10-22_15-16-37.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1.3. Detail configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/How%20to%20Configure%20SAIL%20Port/image-2024-10-22_15-38-26.png?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/How to Configure SAIL Port/image-2024-10-22_15-38-26.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinDirection :  It will define initial direction after Port_Init()."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinDirectionChangeable: Port Pin direction changeable enabled.  API: Port_SetPinDirection()"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinDriveStrength: Drive strength of the GPIO pin."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinDriveStrengthChangeable: True: Port Pin Drive Strength changeable allowed. API: Port_SetPinDriveStrength()"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinInitialMode: This should be check"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "PortPinPullRes: Range: PORT_PIN_NO_PULL = 0 PORT_PIN_PULL_DOWN PORT_PIN_KEEPER PORT_PIN_PULL_UP"
    },
    {
